

				fnt
				===
		

0.  Description.

	FNT is a menu for choosing a "logical font description".

1.  Operation.

	Choose a font or an initial segment of a logical font description.

2.  zûdefine cx

	cx = target context of font menu.
	z = `cx._FNT

3.  Variables
	
	_FNTû	font menu
	_FONTû	label of chosen font

4.  Restrictions

	_FNT and _FONT control their set callbacks

5.  Example

		$load s
		$load fnt

		show fnt.define `
		show `_FONT





